1. What is Linux? List three pros and cons of it.
Linux is an operating system, just like Windows or Mac. What makes it special is that it’s free and open for anyone to use or change.
Three good things about Linux:
•	You don’t have to pay for it.
•	It’s very secure and doesn’t get viruses easily.
•	You can change almost anything about it if you want.
Three not-so-good things:
•	It can be tricky to learn if you’re new.
•	Some popular programs or games might not work on it.
•	Sometimes, new gadgets (like printers) don’t work right away.
